# Backend Rules — Server Layer

> Full contract: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Structure (Non-Negotiable)
```
server/src/
├── core/        → Express app factory + route registry only
├── features/    → domain modules: controllers, models, routes (grouped by feature)
├── shared/      → middleware, utils, validators, config, types
└── index.ts     → server entrypoint (boots express + connects DB)
```

- New domain logic always goes in `server/src/features/<feature-name>/`
- Cross-feature shared logic goes in `server/src/shared/`
- `core/` contains only wire-up, never business logic

## TypeScript Standards
- 100% TypeScript. `allowJs: false` in tsconfig.
- Never use `any`. Use proper interfaces or `unknown` + type guards.
- All Zod schemas must be co-located with the feature that owns them.

## Validation
- Zod is mandatory for all request body/param/query contracts
- Always validate before touching DB or calling services

## Auth & Security
- JWT stored in `HttpOnly` cookies — never `localStorage`
- Reset tokens: raw in email, SHA-256 hash in DB
- CORS dev: dynamic `localhost:*` + `127.0.0.1:*` regex
- CORS prod: explicit whitelist only. Never `origin: *` with `credentials: true`

## Testing
- `strict_tdd: true` — write test before implementation
- Framework: Jest + Supertest
- Run: `pnpm test` from monorepo root

## Build Validation
```bash
pnpm -C server run build   # tsc compile → dist/. Must exit 0.
pnpm test                  # must pass
```
